Q2. For each employee, display the employee number, job, salary, and salary increased by 15% and expressed as a whole number. Label the column New Salary.

Input:- 

SELECT EMP_NO,EMP_NAME,EMP_SAL,EMP_SAL+(EMP_SAL*15/100) "New Salary" FROM EMPLOYEE2
Output:-






Q3. Modify your query no 4. (2) add a column that subtracts the old salary from the new salary. Label the column Increase

Input:- 

SELECT EMP_NO,EMP_NAME,EMP_SAL,EMP_SAL+(EMP_SAL*15/100) "New Salary",(EMP_SAL*15/100) "Increase" FROM EMPLOYEE2
Output:-
